Description: Pottery vase of rough straw tempered Nile silt, with ovoid shape, round base, slightly inset short neck and roll over rim.
Curator's comments: Like Rough Ware R65b in Petrie’s Corpus of Prehistoric Pottery. Grave 154 in the Fort Cemetery was excavated by John Garstang and is published in B. Adams, The Fort Cemetery at Hierakonpolis (1987), p. 158
Acquisition name: Donated by: Frederick George Hilton Price
